$ Stellarium popup: Configuration -> Information

The → Wissenschaft/Astronomie/tools/Stellarium[Stellarium] popop Configuration (reached with the `F2` → Wissenschaft/Astronomie/tools/Stellarium#stellarium-shortcut[shortcut key]) -> Information
allows to choose which data is shown when an object is selected.

The following data items can be chosen:
table { ll
  Name ☰
  Catalog number(s) ☰
  Right ascencion/Decliation (J2000 and of data) ☰
  Hour angle/Declination ☰
  Azimuth/Altitude ☰
  Ecliptic coordinates (J2000 and of date) ☰
  Galactic coordinates ☰
  Supergalactic coordinates ☰
  Additional coordinates (from plugins) ☰
  Elongation ☰
  Visual magnitude ☰
  Absolute magnitude ☰
  Type ☰
  Size ☰
  Velocity ☰
  Proper Motion ☰
  Distance ☰
  Sidereal time ☰
  Constellation ☰
  Rises, transits and sets ☰
  Additional Information ☰
table }

gh|about-Stellarium|/GUI/popups/Configuration/Information.png||

sa:

  The → Wissenschaft/Astronomie/tools/Stellarium/script/API[Stellarium Script API] to select an object is → Wissenschaft/Astronomie/tools/Stellarium/script/API/core/selectObjectByName[`core.selectObjectByName()`].
  -
  The function that allows to turn off or on displaying some information is → Wissenschaft/Astronomie/tools/Stellarium/script/API/core/setSelectedObjectInfo[`core.setSelectedObjectInfo()`].

  → Wissenschaft/Astronomie/tools/Stellarium/GUI/popups/Configuration
